  "text": "Kubernetes RBAC verb coverage audit for kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0\n\n## Verb Definitions\n\nThe Kubernetes RBAC system defines 8 core verbs that can be used in RBAC policies:\n1. **get** - retrieve a single resource\n2. **list** - retrieve a collection of resources\n3. **watch** - monitor changes to resources\n4. **create** - create new resources\n5. **update** - update existing resources\n6. **patch** - partially modify resources\n7. **delete** - delete individual resources\n8. **deletecollection** - delete multiple resources at once\n\nAdditionally, **proxy** is supported for CONNECT operations but is excluded from API discovery.\n\n## Verb Definition Files\n\nVerb constant definitions are located in:\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1/types.go` (line 31): Defines VerbAll = \"*\"\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1alpha1/types.go` (line 31): Defines VerbAll = \"*\"\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/api/rbac/v1beta1/types.go` (line 31): Defines VerbAll = \"*\"\n- `pkg/apis/rbac/types.go` (line 31): Defines VerbAll = \"*\"\n\nVerb group definitions in `plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/bootstrappolicy/policy.go` (lines 36-40):\n- Write = [\"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n- ReadWrite = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\", \"deletecollection\"]\n- Read = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n- ReadUpdate = [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n\n## HTTP to Kube Verb Mapping\n\nThe file `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` defines the mapping from HTTP verbs to Kubernetes verbs at lines 177-189:\n\n```go\nvar toDiscoveryKubeVerb = map[string]string{\n    \"CONNECT\":          \"\",                  // do not list in discovery (proxy)\n    \"DELETE\":           \"delete\",\n    \"DELETECOLLECTION\": \"deletecollection\",\n    \"GET\":              \"get\",\n    \"LIST\":             \"list\",\n    \"PATCH\":            \"patch\",\n    \"POST\":             \"create\",\n    \"PROXY\":            \"proxy\",\n    \"PUT\":              \"update\",\n    \"WATCH\":            \"watch\",            // deprecated in 1.11\n    \"WATCHLIST\":        \"watch\",            // deprecated in 1.11\n}\n```\n\n## Handler Registration and Verb Enforcement\n\nThe API installer in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go` implements comprehensive verb enforcement through:\n\n1. **Interface Detection** (lines 334-344): The installer checks which REST interfaces a storage object implements to determine supported verbs:\n   - `rest.Creater` interface → enables \"POST\" (create)\n   - `rest.Lister` interface → enables \"LIST\" (list)\n   - `rest.Getter` interface → enables \"GET\" (get)\n   - `rest.Updater` interface → enables \"PUT\" (update)\n   - `rest.Patcher` interface → enables \"PATCH\" (patch)\n   - `rest.GracefulDeleter` interface → enables \"DELETE\" (delete)\n   - `rest.CollectionDeleter` interface → enables \"DELETECOLLECTION\" (deletecollection)\n   - `rest.Watcher` interface → enables \"WATCH\" (watch)\n   - `rest.Connecter` interface → enables \"CONNECT\" (proxy)\n\n2. **Handler Registration** (lines 796-1100): Each supported verb has a dedicated handler:\n   - Line 797: GET handler via `restfulGetResource()`\n   - Line 831: LIST handler via `restfulListResource()`\n   - Line 864: PUT handler via `restfulUpdateResource()`\n   - Line 887: PATCH handler via `restfulPatchResource()`\n   - Line 919: POST handler via `restfulCreateResource()`\n   - Line 950: DELETE handler via `restfulDeleteResource()`\n   - Line 979: DELETECOLLECTION handler via `restfulDeleteCollection()`\n   - Line 1006: WATCH handler (deprecated in 1.11)\n   - Line 1047: CONNECT handler\n\n3. **Verb Mapping to API Resources** (line 752): The installer validates each action.Verb against toDiscoveryKubeVerb and includes only valid verbs in API resource discovery.\n\n## RBAC Authorization Enforcement\n\nThe RBAC authorization layer enforces verb constraints at request time:\n\n1. **RuleAllows Function** (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`, line 178):\n   - Calls `rbacv1helpers.VerbMatches()` to check if requested verb matches policy rule\n\n2. **VerbMatches Function** (`pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go`, line 26):\n   - Checks each verb in the policy rule against the requested verb\n   - Returns true if: (1) rule contains VerbAll (\"*\"), OR (2) exact verb match\n   - Returns false if no match\n\n3. **Supporting Match Functions** (`pkg/apis/rbac/v1/evaluation_helpers.go`):\n   - APIGroupMatches (line 39): Validates API group matches\n   - ResourceMatches (line 52): Validates resource matches (including subresources)\n   - ResourceNameMatches (line 80): Validates resource name matches\n   - NonResourceURLMatches (line 94): Validates non-resource URL matches\n\n## Authorization Decision Path\n\nRequest verb authorization flow:\n1. `RBACAuthorizer.Authorize()` method (`plugin/pkg/auth/authorizer/rbac/rbac.go`, line 75) receives authorization request\n2. Fetches applicable PolicyRules for the user\n3. Calls `RuleAllows()` for each rule (line 64)\n4. `RuleAllows()` validates all four constraints: Verb, APIGroup, Resource, and Name\n5. Returns DecisionAllow only if ALL constraints match\n6. Returns DecisionNoOpinion if no matching rule found\n\n## Verb Coverage Analysis\n\n### Complete Coverage of All 8 Verbs\n\nAll 8 core verbs are implemented with:\n1. ✓ Handler registration in installer.go\n2. ✓ HTTP verb mapping in toDiscoveryKubeVerb\n3. ✓ Storage interface abstraction for verb support\n4. ✓ RBAC authorization enforcement via VerbMatches\n5. ✓ Bootstrap policies demonstrating usage in policy.go\n6. ✓ API resource discovery listing verbs\n\n### Verb Constraints Enforced\n\nThe system enforces that:\n- Only verbs that map to implemented storage interfaces are exposed\n- Only verbs in an API resource's APIResource.Verbs list can be used\n- Only verbs in applicable RBAC policy rules are authorized\n- All four constraint dimensions (Verb, APIGroup, Resource, ResourceName) are validated together\n\n### Special Cases\n\n1. **Wildcard Matching**: VerbAll (\"*\") in RBAC rules matches all verbs (line 28 of evaluation_helpers.go)\n2. **Deprecated Verbs**: WATCH and WATCHLIST at item/collection paths are deprecated in 1.11 but still supported\n3. **Proxy Verb**: CONNECT verb maps to \"proxy\" but is excluded from discovery (empty string in map)\n4. **Subresources**: Verb matching works for both parent resources and subresources via ResourceMatches()\n\n## Conclusion\n\nKubernetes v1.32.0 has comprehensive RBAC verb coverage with:\n- Clear verb definitions in multiple versioned RBAC APIs (v1, v1alpha1, v1beta1)\n- Complete handler implementation for all 8 core verbs plus proxy\n- Proper enforcement at both API registration and authorization layers\n- Consistent verb constraint checking across all API operations\n- Bootstrap policies demonstrating proper verb usage patterns\n\nThe system is complete and well-structured for RBAC verb constraint enforcement."
